<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[824,1474,1379,1499]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">A very distinct species characterized by robust growth, small capitula, anthers without pollen, very dark stigmas and numerous narrow erect outer involucral bracts. It is probably the rarest of the subalpine Corsican endemics.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
